{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry represents the type I-D Cas7/Csc2 family of Cas proteins that are strictly associated with the Cyano subtype of CRISPR/Cas locus and found in several species of Cyanobacteria and several archaeal species. This family is designated Csc2 for CRISPR/Cas Subtype Cyano protein 2, as it is often the second gene upstream of the core cas genes, cas3-cas4-cas1-cas2 [[cite:PUB00009737], [cite:PUB00138428], [cite:PUB00150950]]. Structural analysis of T. pendens Csc2 revealed that it forms a core RRM-like domain, flanked by three peripheral insertion domains: a lid domain, a zinc-binding domain and a helical domain. Csc2 binds single-stranded RNA in vitro in a sequence-independent manner [[cite:PUB00138428]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false} {"text" "<p>The CRISPR-Cas system is a prokaryotic defence mechanism against foreign genetic elements. The key elements of this defence system are the Cas proteins and the CRISPR RNA.</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "4txd", "name" "Crystal structure of Thermofilum pendens Csc2"}, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"pfam" {"PF18320" "Csc2 Crispr"}, "ncbifam" {"TIGR03157" "type I-D CRISPR-associated protein Cas7/Csc2"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "CRISPR-associated protein Cas7/Csc2", "short" "CRISPR-assoc_prot_Cas7/Csc2"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 3, "domain_architectures" 2, "proteomes" 192, "taxa" 1437, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 809, "sets" 0, "proteins" 801, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 589}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {"gp" {"displayName" "Genome Properties", "description" "Genome properties is an annotation system whereby functional attributes can be assigned to a genome, based on the presence of a defined set of protein signatures within that genome.", "rank" 45, "